cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for human detection in natural scenes. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a bootstrapping method and uses Convolutional Neural Networks, which are common techniques in the sub-categories cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image processing and feature extraction, which are relevant to the sub-categories cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
